---++ About this Document
Documentation in OSG is provided by a team consisting of people that develop software used by OSG, administer OSG sites, test releases, and are volunteers from VOs.  If you would like to help by volunteering to improve a document are in some other way, please contact this team via their [[mailto:osg-docs@opensciencegrid.org][mailing list]].

We use a document management process/system to create, update, review, and test documents.  Information is provided via the links below for people involved with documentation.

---++ Document Management System
   * *[[Documentation.DocHowTo][Trash.ReleaseDocumentationDocHowTo]]: Overall description of the documentation process and how to do OSG documentation - This single document covers nearly everything*

   * Documentation.DocClassifications: Classification of Documents
   * Documentation.DocManagementVariables: Variables used to manage ownership, review, and testing of documents
   * Documentation.DocTrackingTables: How to create tables to manage documents for which you have some responsibility
   * Documentation.DocProcess: Description of the Documentation Process
   * Documentation.DocReleaseProcess: Description of the Documentation/Software Release Process

---++ For Writers
   * *[[Documentation.DocForOwners][Trash.ReleaseDocumentationDocForOwners]]: Overview for document Owners*
   * *[[Documentation/WebTopicCreator][Create New Documentation Topic]]: Create new document in the Documentation Web*
   * *[[Documentation/Release3/WebTopicCreator][Create New Release3 Topic]]: Create new document in the Release3 Web*

   * Documentation.DocOwnerResponsibilities: Document Owner Responsibilities
   * Documentation.DocWriterAdvice: Advice on how to write good documents
   * Documentation.DocFormattingRules: Very useful information on our standards and TWiki shortcuts

---++ For Reviewers
   * *[[Documentation.DocForReviewers][Trash.ReleaseDocumentationDocForReviewers]]: Overview for Document Reviewers - This single document cover everything for Reviewers*

   * Documentation.DocReviewerResponsibilities: Document Reviewer Responsibilities
   * Documentation.DocFormattingRules:  Very useful information on our standards and TWiki shortcuts

---++ For Testers
   * *[[Documentation.DocForTesters][Trash.ReleaseDocumentationDocForTesters]]: Overview for Document Testers - This single document covers everything for Testers*

   * Documentation.DocTesterResponsibilities: Document Tester Responsibilities

